Currently, the OpenType Feature File Syntax specification is silent on how an implementation should handle zero values. makeotf seems to interpret zero values differently depending on context:

* for a SinglePos statement, a `0` or `<0 0 0 0>` value gets compiled to a ValueRecord format 0;
* for a PairPos statement in a horizontal compilation context, a `0` or `<0 0 0 0>` value gets compiled to a ValueRecord format 4 whose `XAdvance` value is zero;
* for a PairPos statement in a vertical compilation context, a `0` or `<0 0 0 0>` value gets compiled to a ValueRecord format 8 whose `YAdvance` value is zero.

Since this can subtly affect text rendering, I think this should be part of the specification. See https://github.com/fonttools/fonttools/pull/850 for test cases, and https://github.com/fonttools/fonttools/issues/633 for broader context .

