Hi, On Mac OS libc++ specialize std::vector<bool> so it uses bit references instead of bool&. This lead to compilation errors when trying to bind operator[]. For simple cases this of course could be solve by creating lambda functions for setting and getting bool values but inability to bind such functions made binding of template types based on vector<bool> challenging. Not sure if that proper way to solve this but I wonder: would it be possible to solve this on PyBind11 level instead? Perhaps as specialization for binding functions returning std::__1::__bit_reference<...>?

Thanks,

Code to reproduce this:
```c++
// Require Mac OS X + Clang to reproduce

#include <pybind11/pybind11.h>
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>

//using Vector = std::vector<int>; // works fine
using Vector = std::vector<bool>; // lead to compilation error!

namespace py = pybind11;

PYBIND11_PLUGIN(example) {
    py::module m("example", "pybind11 example plugin");

	pybind11::class_<Vector> cl(m, "Vector");

	cl.def("f", [](Vector &v, int i) {
